

What is the Facade Design Pattern?
..................................................................
The Facade Pattern is a Structural Design Pattern that provides a single simplified interface to a complex subsystem.

Definition: The Facade Pattern hides the complexity of multiple classes and exposes one easy-to-use interface to the client.
..................................................................
Real-Time Banking Example
..................................................................
Suppose a customer transfers money.

Without Facade, the application has to call multiple services.
..................................................................
Transfer Money

↓

Account Service

↓

Balance Service

↓

Transaction Service

↓

Notification Service

↓

Audit Service

The client has to know all these services.

With Facade
Customer

↓

BankFacade

↓

Account Service

Balance Service

Transaction Service

Notification Service

Audit Service

The client only calls one method, and the facade coordinates all the internal services.

Step 1: Subsystem Classes
..................................................................
Account Service
public class AccountService {

    public void validateAccount() {

        System.out.println("Account Validated");
    }
}
Balance Service
public class BalanceService {

    public void checkBalance() {

        System.out.println("Balance Verified");
    }
}
Transaction Service
public class TransactionService {

    public void transferMoney() {

        System.out.println("Money Transferred");
    }
}
Notification Service
public class NotificationService {

    public void sendSMS() {

        System.out.println("SMS Sent");
    }
}

Step 2: Facade Class
..................................................................
public class BankFacade {

    private AccountService accountService =
            new AccountService();

    private BalanceService balanceService =
            new BalanceService();

    private TransactionService transactionService =
            new TransactionService();

    private NotificationService notificationService =
            new NotificationService();

    public void transfer() {

        accountService.validateAccount();

        balanceService.checkBalance();

        transactionService.transferMoney();

        notificationService.sendSMS();
    }
}

Step 3: Client
..................................................................
public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        BankFacade bankFacade = new BankFacade();

        bankFacade.transfer();
    }
}
