Another Real-Time Example
Home Theater

Without Facade

Turn on TV

Turn on Speaker

Turn on DVD

Set Volume

Play Movie

With Facade

homeTheater.watchMovie();

One method performs all operations internally.

Spring Boot Example
Payment Service

Instead of calling multiple services from the controller:

paymentService.validate();

paymentService.debit();

paymentService.credit();

paymentService.sendNotification();

Use a Facade:

bankFacade.transferMoney();

The controller remains simple.

Advantages
..................................................................
Simplifies client code.
Hides subsystem complexity.
Promotes loose coupling.
Improves maintainability.
Centralizes business workflow.

Disadvantages
..................................................................
The facade can become too large if it handles too many responsibilities.
It may hide useful subsystem features that some clients need directly.
